snap install ~/Downloads/GitHubDesktop-linux-2.0.4-linux1.snap --classic --dangerous
    # install the git command
    sudo apt-get install -y git
    sudo apt-get install -y git-core
    #clone this repository in the current directory  
    git clone https://github.com/BestSolution-at/fixtar.git
    #installing the build requisites
    sudo apt-get install -y make
    sudo apt-get install -y gcc
    sudo apt-get install -y flex
    sudo apt-get install -y sed
    sudo apt-get install -y coreutils
    # change directory to fixtar/src 
    cd  fixtar/src
    # build from source
    make
    # install the tool in /usr/local/bin
    sudo make install
    sudo apt -f install


----CONFIGURE-YOUR-ACCOUNT-----

After you install Github, use the following two commands by replacing “user_name” with your GitHub username and replacing “email_id” with your email-id you used to create your GitHub account.

With your terminal execute command

 git config –global user.name “user_name”

 git config –global user.email “email_id”

Configuring GitHub

 configure git

 git config --global core.editor "nano -w"

 mkdir ~/git

 cd ~/git

Your are ready for download your repository !!!

 git clone https://github.com/exemple/exemple.git
